The paper proposes a novel approach for generating creative artifacts using a deep neural network. The approach is inspired by the increased association between task-positive and task-negative networks in the brain during the creative process. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The proposed approach involves generating images, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The approach is fully unsupervised, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper involves generating novel and valuable ideas, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
